Death Weeks 11
  1. Click under Visualizations panel on Line and stacked column chart
  2. Click and drag WeekDuration Field onto the Shared Axis for line chart where it says "Add data fields here"
  3. Click and drag .Death Rate  into the Column values Field where it says "Add data fields here"
  4. Click and drag .Death WoW%  into the Line values Field where it says "Add data fields here"
  5. Click and drag Last Twelve Weeks to the Filter on this visual, make sure Last Twelve Weeks is selected 
  6. Make sure .Recovered Rate and .Recovered WoW% are formatted in percentages - Click on the item in the Fields / automatic format should pop up / change Format from General to Percentage


Then click on the Paintbrush (Format) icon under the visualizations pane and configure as seen below

Make sure it is sorted correctly

NOTE** Once you click at the bottom "Customize Series" you will have 2 options to customize 1) Death Rate 2)Death WoW%. These two values can be selected by clicking the down arrow underneath "Customize Series"




Change to Percentages




NOTE** If the dates are still not in order, make sure that WeekDuration is sorted by WeeksEnd in Data view
